conclusion: Car A enters from the lower right direction towards the blocks.
Car A is aimed roughly at the orange tower that is just right of centre.
First contact is the lower (larger) orange block of the tower.
The small orange cube on top is knocked off to the left.
The large orange block only shifts a little because it is heavier and broad-based.
The car's remaining momentum is small; it pushes the large orange block a few centimetres backward and then stops.
The car stops with its nose touching the face of the large orange block.
Blocks struck: both blocks of the orange two-block tower (large bottom block and small top cube).
Final resting place of car A: directly in front of the large orange block, slightly above the tower's original position.
